content:
During the next Community Call, we will hear from @lonnibesancon, who has conducted multiple meta-research projects and written opinion pieces focussed on unreliable science or fraudulent data.
https://asapbio.org/event/november-2023-community-call-the-trials-and-tribulations-of-post-publication-peer-review

In response to Lonni's rigorous and scientific approaches, he has faced lawsuits and attacks from senior scientists.
The talk from Lonni about his experiences will be followed by a longer discussion.

#ECRs #preprint #preprints #research #science #OpenScience

Revising isn’t the same as editing – and that’s much more important than it sounds

The other day, I was pounding the keyboard as I drafted what will become Chapter 5 of my (coauthored) new book, Helping Students Write. As often happens to me, I hesitated over word choice: I typed “revising”, backed up and replaced it with “editing”,* backed up again and reinstated “revising”, and then finally scolded myself for worrying about word choice at all while pounding out a…

content:
Take energy: we've all heard that Americans use *far* more energy than most of their foreign cousins (Canadians and Norwegians are even more energy-hungry, thanks to their heating bills).

The idea of providing every person on Earth with the energy abundance of an average Canadian is a horrifying prospect - provided that your energy generation is coupled to your carbon emissions. But there are *lots* of renewable sources of energy.

15/

content:
Magnum, p.i.–1980s series gets its own Playmobil set

It took four decades, but Magnum, p.i. is getting its own Playmobil playset.  It's based on the original series, not the current show.  As one of the most successful TV reboots ever winds down this year, the original Magnum, Higgins, T.C., and Rick have been shrunk into recognizable Playmobil people. You can almost hear Higgins shouting, "Oh, my GOD!" as Thomas speeds this new reproduction of Robin Masters' red…
